{"title_page": "List of hockey world championships", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Orphan|date=October 2015}}\n\n'''Hockey world championships''' include:\n\n==On the ground==\n\n===Field hockey===\n* [[Hockey World Cup]]\n* [[Women's Hockey World Cup]]\n* [[Hockey Champions Trophy]]\n\n===Indoor field hockey===\n* [[Indoor Hockey World Cup]]\n\n==On ice==\n\n===Ice hockey===\n* [[Ice Hockey World Championships]], the most important IIHF international ice-hockey competitions\n* [[World Pond Hockey Championships]], playing the pond hockey variant of ice-hockey\n* [[IIHF World U18 Championship]], for ice-hockey\n* [[IIHF World Women's Championships|IIHF World Women Championship]], for ice-hockey\n* [[IIHF World Women's U18 Championships]], for ice hockey\n* [[IIHF World U20 Championship]] (World Junior Hockey Championship), for ice-hockey\n* [[Ice-hockey at the Winter Olympics]] had world championship status until 1976\n\n===Sledge hockey===\n* [[Ice sledge hockey#See also|IPC Ice Sledge Hockey World Championships]], for sledge hockey\n\n===Bandy===\nBandy is also sometimes called \"Russian hockey\", \"hockey with ball\" or \"winter football\"\n* [[Bandy World Championship]]\n* [[Women's Bandy World Championship]]\n* [[Youth Bandy World Championship]]\n** [[Bandy World Championship G-17]]\n** [[Bandy World Championship Y-19]]\n** [[Bandy World Championship Y-23]]\n* [[Bandy World Cup]]\n* [[Bandy World Cup Women]]\n\n==On floors==\n\n===Roller hockey===\n* [[Rink Hockey World Championship]], for Roller hockey (Quad)\n* [[Ladies Rink Hockey World Championship]] (CIRH Women's World Cup), for Roller hockey (Quad)\n* [[Rink Hockey World Championship U-20]], for Roller hockey (Quad)\n* [[Rink hockey World Club Championship]], for Roller hockey (Quad)\n* [[IIHF InLine Hockey World Championship]], for Roller hockey (Inline)\n* [[International Roller Sports Federation \u2013 Inline|FIRS Men's Inline Hockey World Championship]] (FIRS World Championships), for Roller hockey (Inline)\n* [[International Roller Sports Federation \u2013 Inline|FIRS Inline Hockey World Junior Championships]], for Roller hockey (Inline)\n* [[International Roller Sports Federation \u2013 Inline|FIRS Inline Hockey World Women Championships]], for Roller hockey (Inline)\n\n===Floorball===\n* [[Floorball World Championships]]\n\n==On table tops==\n\n===Table hockey===\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Championship history|World Championship/s]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Women Championship history|World Women Championship/s]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Junior Championship history|World Junior Championship/s]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Veteran Championship history|World Veteran/Senior Championship/s]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Men.27s Team Championship history|World Men's Team Championship]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Women.27s Team Championship history|World Women's Team Championship]], for ITHF table hockey\n* [[ITHF table hockey#World Club Championship history|World Club Championship]], for ITHF table hockey\n\n===Air hockey===\n* [[Air hockey#Tournament History|World Championships]], for air hockey\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ice hockey at the Olympic Games]]\n* [[Field hockey at the Summer Olympics]]\n*[[World Cup (disambiguation)|World Cup]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hockey world championships}}\n[[Category:Variations of hockey|*]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey-related lists|World championships]]\n[[Category:Field hockey-related lists|World championships]]\n[[Category:World championships in hockey variants| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Orphan|date=October 2015}}\n\n'''Hockey world championships''' include:\n\n==On the ground==\n\n===Field hockey===\n* [[Hockey World Cup]]\n* [[Women's Hockey World Cup]]\n* [[Hockey Champions Trophy]]\n\n===Indoor field hockey===\n* [[Indoor Hockey World Cup]]\n\